1. Overview
A high-fidelity web application prototype for ordering pizza, heavily inspired by the "Pizzy" Dribbble interaction. It allows users to browse a menu, see nutritional data, and "checkout" by sending order details directly to the owner via email or a dashboard.

2. User Features (Functional Requirements)
Hero Menu: Display pizzas with high-quality rotating images (matching the Dribbble vibe).

Nutritional Overlay: A toggle or "info" icon for each item showing Calories, Protein, Carbs, and Fats.

Pizzy Interaction: The "Add to Cart" button must morph into a +/- counter (as seen in the design).

Cart System: Real-time price calculation including tax and a "dummy" delivery fee.

Checkout Flow: * Address Input (Manual text field).

Payment Selection: Cash or UPI.

Note: If UPI is selected, show a static QR code or a "Pay on Delivery via UPI" message.

Order Confirmation: A "Success" animation after clicking "Place Order."

3. Owner Features
Order Routing: When a user clicks "Place Order," the system sends the full order (Item, Quantity, Address, Total) to your email.

